{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04415/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04415"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:44:15"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, pan"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man yells frantically at figures offscreen."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04415","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04415"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/canvas/1/c0ddc1ef-12cc-4034-95b0-11e1aa519fb4","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:12:01.067Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As Reynolds lashes out at his staff, the music has shifted. Strings rise and become almost percussive. The dressmaker also says, “You’re no good to me just standing there, Pippa. I need your hands on there.” He is referring to the outfit he is prepping on one of the models, of course, but hands are a crucial motif throughout the film; they are what drives both Reynolds’s artistry and Alma’s ability to take control through poisoning Reynolds. Reynolds’s complaint that Pippa shouldn’t just be standing around recalls Alma’s claim that she can “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW234411001 BCX4\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-03446.html\"><u>stand longer</u></a>” than anyone else. At times Reynolds does indeed want his models to simply be statues, standing for long periods of time to showcase his wares as well as allowing him to design his clothing. However, it’s Alma’s ability to endure and to test Reynolds’s patience by “standing” literally and metaphorically standing up to him that allows her to stand out.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04415/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:691.2516823687752,97.46971736204586,736.4737550471064,790.7402422611035"}}}]}]}]}